1419
02:06:54,092 --> 02:06:55,544
They hate the Chinese.

1420
02:06:56,420 --> 02:07:00,590
Maybe they hate Americans less
than the Russians and the Chinese.

1421
02:07:00,967 --> 02:07:02,668
I mean, if tomorrow
the Vietnamese are communists,

1422
02:07:02,768 --> 02:07:05,010
they will be Vietnamese communists.

1423
02:07:05,637 --> 02:07:08,347
And this is something
that you never understood, you Americans.

1424
02:07:09,057 --> 02:07:11,342
I don't know. Maybe in the future

1425
02:07:11,442 --> 02:07:13,894
we can make something with the Viet Minh.

1426
02:07:14,146 --> 02:07:15,729
Don't you understand?

1427
02:07:16,064 --> 02:07:18,774
The VC say, "Go away! Go away!"

1428
02:07:18,900 --> 02:07:21,602
That's finished for all the white people
in Indochina.

1429
02:07:21,702 --> 02:07:24,864
If you're French, American,
that's all the same.

1430
02:07:25,073 --> 02:07:28,742
Go! They want to forget you. Look at them.

1431
02:07:30,871 --> 02:07:33,621
Look, this is the truth. An egg.

1432
02:07:36,792 --> 02:07:38,334
The white left.

1433
02:07:39,837 --> 02:07:41,713
The yellow stay.

1434
02:07:49,763 --> 02:07:50,922
When I was in Saigon,

1435
02:07:51,022 --> 02:07:54,759
I spoke to an American politician
and he explained it very well.

1436
02:07:54,859 --> 02:07:58,471
He said, "Look, yesterday it was Korea,

1437
02:07:58,571 --> 02:08:04,443
"today, Vietnam, tomorrow, Thailand,
the Philippines, and then maybe Europe."

1438
02:08:07,113 --> 02:08:08,230
Why not Europe?

1439
02:08:08,330 --> 02:08:10,699
Look what happened
in Czechoslovakia recently!

1440
02:08:10,867 --> 02:08:12,484
And even before the Second World War,

1441
02:08:12,584 --> 02:08:14,653
the Americans knew
exactly what was going on.

1442
02:08:14,753 --> 02:08:17,164
They don't want that shit to take over!

1443
02:08:20,084 --> 02:08:24,580
- All you white people are shit.
- They are fighting. Fighting for freedom.

1444
02:08:24,680 --> 02:08:26,797
Freedom? Bullshit.

1445
02:08:27,174 --> 02:08:29,884
French bullshit. American bullshit.

1446
02:08:30,344 --> 02:08:32,053
Dien Bien Phu is a trap.

1447
02:08:32,888 --> 02:08:35,973
All soldiers know they are already dead.

1448
02:08:38,018 --> 02:08:39,936
You know anything about Dien Bien Phu?

1449
02:08:43,065 --> 02:08:47,018
- Yeah, I know.
- No, you don't, not really.

1450
02:08:47,118 --> 02:08:50,112
Dien Bien Phu was an error, you know?
A military mistake.

1451
02:08:50,239 --> 02:08:53,907
A mistake? A voluntary mistake! Voluntary!

1452
02:08:56,619 --> 02:09:00,580
All the soldiers knew.
We knew we would be dead.

1453
02:09:01,332 --> 02:09:03,075
Generals and colonels
believe it's impossible

1454
02:09:03,175 --> 02:09:07,462
for the Viets to get a cannon
up there in the mountains, but they do.

1455
02:09:08,214 --> 02:09:11,007
Then they wait for the rain to come.

1456
02:09:12,176 --> 02:09:16,221
When it comes, no airplane can fly there.

1457
02:09:16,430 --> 02:09:22,051
And our paratroopers jump at 90 meters.
I mean, you know, 90 meters, 70 meters...

1458
02:09:22,151 --> 02:09:25,312
I mean, that's crazy.
No army in the world can do that.

1459
02:09:25,897 --> 02:09:29,358
And they only do that
to be dead with their friends.

1460
02:09:31,361 --> 02:09:32,695
No, no!

1461
02:09:35,865 --> 02:09:38,033
The French army was sacrificed,

1462
02:09:38,243 --> 02:09:40,945
sacrificed by the politicians safe at home.

1463
02:09:41,045 --> 02:09:43,747
They put the army in an impossible
situation where they couldn't win.

1464
02:09:44,958 --> 02:09:48,451
The students are marching in Paris,
protesting, demonstrating.

1465
02:09:48,551 --> 02:09:50,670
They stab the soldiers in the back.

1466
02:09:50,796 --> 02:09:54,674
The soldier would open the grenade,
it wouldn't work.

1467
02:09:54,967 --> 02:09:56,759
A piece of paper would fall.

1468
02:09:59,138 --> 02:10:02,390
Union of French Women.
"We are for the Viets."

1469
02:10:02,683 --> 02:10:03,933
Traitors.

1470
02:10:04,393 --> 02:10:06,519
Communist traitors at home.

1471
02:10:07,938 --> 02:10:09,480
Dien Bien Phu...

1472
02:10:09,857 --> 02:10:12,400
Okay, the French is shit.

1473
02:10:14,528 --> 02:10:16,820
No one cares. No one wants to.

1474
02:10:19,449 --> 02:10:23,410
Why don't you Americans learn from us?
From our mistakes?

1475
02:10:23,745 --> 02:10:25,738
Mon dieu, with your army,
your strength, your power,

1476
02:10:25,838 --> 02:10:27,039
you can win if you want to.

1477
02:10:30,084 --> 02:10:31,501
You can win.

1478
02:10:34,714 --> 02:10:37,924
You know,
I'm sure we can make something there.

1479
02:10:38,676 --> 02:10:40,260
I'm sure about it, you know?

1480
02:10:40,803 --> 02:10:43,346
I never do something wrong
to the people here.

1481
02:10:43,930 --> 02:10:47,350
I'm sorry, you know, but the communists
at home have never been traitors.

1482
02:11:21,300 --> 02:11:24,636
Excuse me. I have to go.
Captain, good night.

1483
02:11:24,970 --> 02:11:27,547
- I was a socialist, you know?
- I know we can stay.

1484
02:11:27,647 --> 02:11:31,643
I know that we can stay. We can stay.

1485
02:11:34,563 --> 02:11:37,932
You know, we always help the people.

1486
02:11:38,032 --> 02:11:39,733
We work with the people.

1487
02:11:56,292 --> 02:12:00,421
See, Captain, when my grandfather

1488
02:12:01,881 --> 02:12:04,133
and my uncles and father came here,

1489
02:12:06,718 --> 02:12:09,303
there was nothing. Nothing.

1490
02:12:10,681 --> 02:12:12,849
The Vietnamese were nothing.

1491
02:12:14,768 --> 02:12:18,521
So, we worked hard, very hard.

1492
02:12:18,689 --> 02:12:23,484
We brought the rubber from Brazil
and then planted it here.

1493
02:12:24,403 --> 02:12:27,697
We took the Vietnamese, work with them,

1494
02:12:28,115 --> 02:12:29,449
make something.

1495
02:12:30,200 --> 02:12:32,201
Something out of nothing.

1496
02:12:33,786 --> 02:12:37,456
So when you ask me
why we want to stay here, Captain,

1497
02:12:39,041 --> 02:12:41,452
we want to stay here because it's ours.

1498
02:12:41,552 --> 02:12:43,003
It belongs to us.

1499
02:12:43,713 --> 02:12:45,380
It keeps our family together.

1500
02:12:47,133 --> 02:12:49,134
I mean, we fight for that.

1501
02:12:51,053 --> 02:12:52,846
While you Americans,

1502
02:12:53,764 --> 02:12:58,643
you are fighting
for the biggest nothing in history.

1503
02:13:06,610 --> 02:13:08,360
I'm sorry, Captain.

1504
02:13:08,862 --> 02:13:13,574
I will see if your men
need any help to repair your boat

1505
02:13:13,867 --> 02:13:17,244
so that you can go on with your war.

1506
02:13:52,404 --> 02:13:55,072
I apologize for my family, Captain.

1507
02:13:57,116 --> 02:13:59,243
We have all lost much here.

1508
02:14:00,787 --> 02:14:03,872
Hubert, his wife and two sons.

1509
02:14:08,294 --> 02:14:10,462
And I have lost a husband.

1510
02:14:16,386 --> 02:14:20,180
- I understand.
- You are tired of the war.

1511
02:14:22,267 --> 02:14:24,392
I can see on your face.

1512
02:14:27,020 --> 02:14:31,148
It was the same in the eyes
of the soldiers of our war.

1513
02:14:32,359 --> 02:14:33,401
We call them...

1514
02:14:36,530 --> 02:14:38,322
"The lost soldiers."

1515
02:14:43,203 --> 02:14:45,746
If you like, we can have some cognac.

1516
02:14:50,501 --> 02:14:51,101
No.

1517
02:14:52,545 --> 02:14:55,505
I'll see about my men and...

1518
02:15:03,306 --> 02:15:05,890
The war will be still here tomorrow.

1519
02:15:16,652 --> 02:15:18,694
Yeah, I guess you're right.

1520
02:15:26,703 --> 02:15:29,371
I noticed you had no wine at dinner.

1521
02:15:30,624 --> 02:15:33,292
No, I don't drink wine.

1522
02:15:36,713 --> 02:15:41,216
I do like cognac,
but I don't want any now, thank you.

1523
02:15:44,845 --> 02:15:47,597
Well, then I must drink alone.

1524
02:15:57,900 --> 02:16:01,277
Will you go back, after the war, to America?

1525
02:16:05,240 --> 02:16:08,242
- No.
- Then you're like us.

1526
02:16:08,494 --> 02:16:10,161
Your home is here.

1527
02:16:27,762 --> 02:16:31,682
Do you know why you can never
step into the same river twice?

1528
02:16:33,935 --> 02:16:37,104
Yeah, 'cause it's always moving.

1529
02:16:38,523 --> 02:16:41,649
I used to prepare a pipe for my husband.

1530
02:16:48,949 --> 02:16:53,244
It was the morphine he took
for the wounds he suffered in his heart.

1531
02:16:56,915 --> 02:17:00,543
He would rage and he would cry,
my lost soldier.

1532
02:17:04,297 --> 02:17:05,965
And I said to him,

1533
02:17:06,717 --> 02:17:10,093
"There are two of you, don't you see?

1534
02:17:11,178 --> 02:17:14,806
"One that kills and one that loves."

1535
02:17:16,934 --> 02:17:18,601
And he said to me,

1536
02:17:19,478 --> 02:17:23,106
"I don't know whether
I am an animal or a god."

1537
02:17:26,569 --> 02:17:28,194
But you are both.

1538
02:18:10,068 --> 02:18:11,819
You want more?

1539
02:18:17,534 --> 02:18:21,370
All that matters is that you are alive.

1540
02:18:23,040 --> 02:18:24,957
You are alive, Captain.

1541
02:18:29,253 --> 02:18:30,879
That's the truth.

1542
02:19:44,785 --> 02:19:48,288
There are two of you, don't you see?

1543
02:19:49,623 --> 02:19:53,792
One that kills and one that loves.

1544
02:20:23,155 --> 02:20:25,698
Can't see nothing. We're stopping.

1545
02:20:26,199 --> 02:20:28,568
You're not authorized
to stop this boat, Chief.

1546
02:20:28,668 --> 02:20:31,495
I said I can't see a thing, Captain.
I'm stopping this boat.

1547
02:20:32,247 --> 02:20:33,823
I ain't risking no more lives.

1548
02:20:33,923 --> 02:20:36,834
I'm in command here, God damn it.
You'll do what I say.

1549
02:20:39,004 --> 02:20:41,172
You see anything, Chef?

1550
02:20:43,175 --> 02:20:45,509
Why don't they fucking attack, man?

1551
02:21:04,737 --> 02:21:06,863
Watch it over here, Chief.

1552
02:21:07,990 --> 02:21:09,658
Got a stump.

1553
02:21:11,077 --> 02:21:12,452
Lance, on the .50s.

1554
02:21:14,245 --> 02:21:16,038
He was close.

1555
02:21:18,083 --> 02:21:19,750
He was real close.

1556
02:21:22,045 --> 02:21:26,916
I couldn't see him yet, but I could feel him,
as if the boat were being sucked upriver

1557
02:21:27,016 --> 02:21:29,885
and the water was flowing back
into the jungle.

1558
02:21:32,430 --> 02:21:34,840
Whatever was going to happen,

1559
02:21:34,940 --> 02:21:38,894
it wasn't gonna be
the way they called it back in Nha Trang.

1560
02:21:43,565 --> 02:21:44,808
Arrows!

1561
02:21:44,908 --> 02:21:45,908
Fire!

1562
02:21:48,237 --> 02:21:49,487
Chef, open up! Fire!

1563
02:21:54,618 --> 02:21:56,577
Lance, fire!

1564
02:22:04,420 --> 02:22:07,714
Chef! Chef, it's okay. Quit firing.

1565
02:22:08,215 --> 02:22:09,798
They're just little toy arrows.

1566
02:22:10,091 --> 02:22:12,009
Cut it out! Quiet!

1567
02:22:12,260 --> 02:22:14,511
Chief, tell them to hold their fire!

1568
02:22:14,929 --> 02:22:17,264
They're just little sticks.
They're just trying to scare us.

1569
02:22:17,682 --> 02:22:18,882
Quiet!

1570
02:22:20,059 --> 02:22:22,845
You got us in this mess,
and now you can't get us out

1571
02:22:22,945 --> 02:22:24,855
because you don't know
where the hell you're going, do you?

1572
02:22:25,440 --> 02:22:26,606
Do you?

1573
02:22:27,608 --> 02:22:30,485
You son of a bitch! You bastard!

1574
02:22:32,113 --> 02:22:34,448
- Lance, get the wheel!
- Fire!

1575
02:22:35,116 --> 02:22:38,659
You savages!
Come and get it, you son of a bitches!

1576
02:22:59,139 --> 02:23:00,739
A spear.

1577
02:24:20,259 --> 02:24:23,094
My mission is to make it up into Cambodia.

1578
02:24:23,720 --> 02:24:26,171
There's a Green Beret colonel up there
who's gone insane

1579
02:24:26,271 --> 02:24:28,140
and I'm supposed to kill him.

1580
02:24:29,559 --> 02:24:32,227
That's fucking typical! Shit!

1581
02:24:32,603 --> 02:24:34,563
Fucking Vietnam mission!

1582
02:24:34,897 --> 02:24:38,642
I'm short and we gotta go up there
so you can kill one of our own guys?

1583
02:24:38,742 --> 02:24:42,571
That's fucking great!
That's just fucking great, man.

1584
02:24:43,322 --> 02:24:46,199
Shit! That's fucking crazy.

1585
02:24:46,784 --> 02:24:49,744
I mean, I thought
you were going in to blow up a bridge

1586
02:24:49,871 --> 02:24:52,747
or some fucking railroad tracks
or something.

1587
02:24:53,748 --> 02:24:55,783
- Sorry.
- No, no, wait, wait.

1588
02:24:55,883 --> 02:24:59,162
We'll go together on the boat.
We'll go with you.

1589
02:24:59,262 --> 02:25:02,923
We'll go up there, but on the boat. Okay?

1590
02:26:09,989 --> 02:26:13,951
Part of me was afraid of what I would find
and what I would do when I got there.

1591
02:26:16,995 --> 02:26:21,457
I knew the risks, or imagined I knew.

1592
02:26:24,002 --> 02:26:28,172
But the thing I felt the most,
much stronger than fear,

1593
02:26:29,800 --> 02:26:31,717
was the desire to confront him.

1594
02:27:44,413 --> 02:27:45,705
Just keep moving.

1595
02:27:46,415 --> 02:27:50,084
Lance, keep your hands
away from the guns.

1596
02:29:17,002 --> 02:29:20,171
It's all right! It's all right!
It's all been approved!

1597
02:29:21,340 --> 02:29:24,592
I ain't coming in there!
Them bastards attacked us!

1598
02:29:26,011 --> 02:29:29,263
Zap them with your siren, man.
Zap them with your siren.

1599
02:29:39,691 --> 02:29:41,525
There's mines over there
and mines over there, too.

1600
02:29:41,693 --> 02:29:44,153
And watch out. Those goddamn monkeys
bite you, I'll tell you.

1601
02:29:45,029 --> 02:29:47,531
That's a pretty one.
Move it right in toward me.

1602
02:29:48,950 --> 02:29:50,868
I'm an American. Yeah.

1603
02:29:51,161 --> 02:29:52,828
An American civilian. Hi, Yanks.

1604
02:29:53,538 --> 02:29:55,037
Hi, American.

1605
02:29:55,539 --> 02:29:56,956
American civilian. It's all right.

1606
02:29:57,708 --> 02:30:00,626
And you got the cigarettes.
And that's what I've been dreaming about.

1607
02:30:01,795 --> 02:30:02,795
Chef.

1608
02:30:03,630 --> 02:30:06,299
- Who are you?
- Who are you?

1609
02:30:10,596 --> 02:30:12,221
I'm a photojournalist.

1610
02:30:12,890 --> 02:30:14,891
I've covered the war since '64.

1611
02:30:15,267 --> 02:30:17,810
I've been in Laos, Cambodia and Nam.

1612
02:30:22,482 --> 02:30:25,233
I'll tell you one thing,
this boat is a mess, man.

1613
02:30:26,235 --> 02:30:27,561
Who are all these people?

1614
02:30:27,661 --> 02:30:32,741
Yeah, they think you've come
to take him away,

1615
02:30:33,075 --> 02:30:35,952
- and I hope that isn't true.
- Take who away?

1616
02:30:38,247 --> 02:30:40,999
Him! Colonel Kurtz.

1617
02:30:42,043 --> 02:30:44,753
These are all his children, man,
as far as you can see.

1618
02:30:46,047 --> 02:30:48,548
Hell, man, out here, we're all his children.

1619
02:30:49,466 --> 02:30:52,843
Could we talk to Colonel Kurtz?

1620
02:30:53,428 --> 02:30:59,099
Hey, man, you don't talk to the Colonel.
Well, you listen to him.

1621
02:31:00,602 --> 02:31:02,603
The man's enlarged my mind.

1622
02:31:03,480 --> 02:31:06,849
He's a poet warrior in the classic sense.

1623
02:31:06,949 --> 02:31:10,144
Sometimes you'll say hello to him, right,

1624
02:31:10,244 --> 02:31:12,605
and he'll just walk right by you
and he won't even notice you.

1625
02:31:12,705 --> 02:31:16,192
And then suddenly he'll grab you,
he'll throw you in a corner and he'll say,

1626
02:31:16,292 --> 02:31:19,361
"Do you know that 'if' is the middle word
in 'life'? If you can keep your head

1627
02:31:19,461 --> 02:31:21,238
"when all about you are losing theirs
and blaming it on you,

1628
02:31:21,338 --> 02:31:22,789
"if you can trust yourself
when all men doubt you..."

1629
02:31:24,083 --> 02:31:27,293
I'm a little man. I'm a little man.
He's a great man.

1630
02:31:28,087 --> 02:31:33,833
"I should have been a pair of ragged claws
Scuttling across the floors of silent seas."

1631
02:31:33,933 --> 02:31:35,468
Stay with the boat.

1632
02:31:36,387 --> 02:31:39,264
Don't go without me, okay?
I wanna get a picture.

1633
02:31:41,809 --> 02:31:46,478
He can be terrible, he can be mean,
and he can be right.

1634
02:31:47,480 --> 02:31:50,315
He's fighting the war. He's a great man.

1635
02:31:58,408 --> 02:32:01,618
I wish I had words, you know?
I wish I had words.

1636
02:32:02,036 --> 02:32:04,580
I can tell you something,
like, the other day he wanted to kill me.

1637
02:32:05,206 --> 02:32:07,416
- Something like that.
- Why'd he want to kill you?

1638
02:32:07,917 --> 02:32:09,501
Because I took his picture.

1639
02:32:10,503 --> 02:32:12,795
He said, "If you take my picture again,

1640
02:32:14,172 --> 02:32:17,800
"I'm gonna kill you," and he meant it.

1641
02:32:20,554 --> 02:32:24,515
So you just lay cool.
Play it cool, laid back. Dig it.

1642
02:32:25,142 --> 02:32:26,851
He gets friendly again. He really does.

1643
02:32:28,478 --> 02:32:30,855
But you don't judge the Colonel.

1644
02:32:31,773 --> 02:32:33,899
You don't judge the Colonel
like an ordinary man.

1645
02:32:40,865 --> 02:32:42,866
Okay, watch it now. These are Americans.

1646
02:32:42,992 --> 02:32:43,992
Americans!

1647
02:32:44,327 --> 02:32:45,827
You can feel the vibe of this place.

1648
02:32:46,829 --> 02:32:50,248
Let me take your picture.
Could you hold... Hello? Hello?

1649
02:32:50,374 --> 02:32:51,875
Could you hold up a minute?

1650
02:33:14,230 --> 02:33:15,397
Colby.

1651
02:33:31,873 --> 02:33:32,956
The heads.

1652
02:33:33,999 --> 02:33:39,212
You're looking at the heads.
Sometimes he goes too far.

1653
02:33:40,089 --> 02:33:41,923
He's the first one to admit it.

1654
02:33:43,050 --> 02:33:45,301
- He's gone crazy.
- Wrong, wrong!

1655
02:33:47,262 --> 02:33:50,215
If you could have heard the man
just two days ago.

1656
02:33:50,315 --> 02:33:54,769
If you could have heard him then, God...
You're gonna call him crazy?

1657
02:33:55,437 --> 02:33:56,813
